  "prompt": "What does \"AAA\" mean in AAA title game?",
  "response": "In the context of video games, \"AAA\" (pronounced \"triple A\") refers to a high-budget, high-profile game produced by a major studio. These games typically have large development teams, extensive marketing campaigns, and significant financial backing. AAA titles are often associated with polished gameplay, cutting-edge graphics, and broad appeal, aiming to achieve commercial success and widespread recognition. Examples of AAA games include titles like \"Call of Duty,\" \"Grand Theft Auto,\" and \"The Legend of Zelda.\"",
